d03d242b-3388-4a93-85a2-7e532f422881.text:
Psalm 109 was written about when Doeg killed all those who were in the priestly city of Nob, and betraying the location of David. This explains why Psalm 109 was so aggressive/vengeful (to put it lightly).
Note that he asks ***GOD*** to do it, and does not do it himself.
Doeg did the same thing to the city of Nob that Saul should have done to the Amalekites
In both times, there was one guy left - Doeg: Abiathar was accidentally spared - Saul: The king of the Amalekites was spared
